text: Participants were randomly assigned 1:1 to the intervention (n = 150) or control (n = 152) arms by using a computer program designed to minimize the likelihood of an imbalance between the study arms with respect to sexual experience and sexual identity. 21 Participants, but not researchers, were blind to arm allocation.
